Task:
Language identifying for English, French and Italian by applying letter/word bigram model. Specifically, the word bigram model utilizes add-one/Laplace smoothing to cope with words unseen in the training corpus.

Instructions:
Run the programs individually within the lang_identifier folder. The output of each program is saved in letterLangId.out and wordLangId.out respectively.
The test.py file is a simple file that calculates the accuracy of each model.
The testing sub-folder provides a sample test consisting sentences in English/French/Italian.
